@node "Requirements"

PtpDigCam software requires the following elements in order to be able to run :

@{b}Hardware:@{ub}

   A Pegasos with a USB port,
   A PTP compliant digital camera linked to the USB port.

@{b}Software:@{ub}

   MorphOS V1.4+
   LayGroup MUI custom class available on Aminet

@endnode

@node "Usage"

PtpDigCam software is started by clicking the icon or by a command line
from shell.

It supports the following settings parameters (tooltypes or shell argument) :

********************************************************************************
 Description            | Standard key           | Short key    | Default value
                        | (tooltype or arg.)     | (arg. only)  |
********************************************************************************
 Default download path  | SAVE_LOCATION          | SAVDIR       | RAM:
 at starting            |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Automatic scan at      | START_AUTO_SCAN        | AUTSCA       | TRUE
 starting               |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Start without unknown  | START_UNKNOWN_NO_WARN  | UNKOK        | FALSE
 device warning         |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 PTP transfer packet    | PACKET_MAX_SIZE        | PKTMAX       | 524288 bytes
 maximum size           |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Delay to retry on      | RESP_ERR_RETRY_DELAY_MS| RETTMS       | 0 ms
 response error         |                        |              |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Use Canon specific     | CANON_DELETE_EVENT     | DELEVT       | FALSE
 delete principle       |                        |              |
********************************************************************************

After program starting, a user interface appears on the Ambient screen :

   The top left "Camera" part provides the currently connected camera
   identification information. Vendor name, model name and serial number read
   from the camera.
 
   The top right "Status" part provides the number of images, videos and
   sounds currently available inside the camera.

   The bar button "Scan" allows to display the camera contents preview and
   detail in the dedicated register pages. The automatic starting scan can be
   disabled with matching setting parameter.
   
   The bar button "All" allows to select all in the camera contents selection
   current page.

   The bar button "None" allows to unselect all in the camera contents selection
   current page.

   The camera contents selection pages allows to select one or several objects
   for action.

   The selected drawer indicates the location where object must be downloaded.
   This location can be changed thanks to the drawer selection gadget. The
   default path at starting can be defined with the matching setting parameter.

   The bar button "Download" allows to start downloading the selected objects
   from the camera.

   The bar button "Delete" allows to start deleting the selected objects inside
   the camera after a user confirmation.

   The bar button "Get date" allows to read the camera current date.

   The bar button "Set date" allows to send the current computer date to force
   the camera to update its current date with.

   The text field at the bottom of the window gives the last performed action
   result.

   During downloading action, if an existing object at location is met, a user
   selection box is opened to let the user select if :
      - The current existing object download must be skipped,
      - The current and any other existing object download must be skipped,
      - The current existing object must be downloaded and overwritten,
      - The current and any other existing object must be downloaded and
        overwritten.  

   During deleting action, if an object is write protected (the device should
   refuse the delete command), a selection box is opened to let the user select
   if :
      - The current protected object deleting must be skipped,
      - The current and any other protected object must be skipped.

Any object (image, video or sound) downloaded from the camera is saved with the
given capture name, size and date.

@endnode

@node "History"

2006.08.27   V2.1   Public release.
                    - Make three camera support levels (specific camera, standard
                      supported vendor camera, unknown vendor camera) insteed of one
                      specific definition for each camera model (too much work)
                    - Remove useless START_UNTESTED_NO_WARN setting
                    - Add progress bar for camera contents scanning
                    - Add camera objects thumbnail processing with default image
                    - Add register pages for thumbnails display and details list display
                    - Move buttons into a bar
                    - Complete buttons with images
                    - Rewrite debug component to add dynamic settings

2006.03.30   V2.0a  Public release.
                    - Casio EX-S500 supported
                    - Fuji S5500 and S7000 referenced (untested)
                    - Fuji and Casio vendor referenced
                    - Canon A310, A510, A610 and A620 referenced (untested)
                    - Canon A60, A400, A410 and A520 supported
                    - Kodak CX7525 supported
                    - Kodak DX6440, DX7440, C300, C310, C315, C340 and V550 referenced
                      (untested)
                    - Tooltype and argument "CANON_DELETE_EVENT" to remove object deleting
                      issue with most of Canon camera (default FALSE)
                    - Tooltype and argument "START_UNKNOWN_NO_WARN" to start without
                      warning message when device is unknown (default FALSE)
                    - Tooltype and argument "START_UNTESTED_NO_WARN" to start without
                      warning message when device is untested (default FALSE)
                    - Rework error notification to the user and displayed result
                    - Enhance PTP protocole error detection (check frame type and check
                      identifier coherence in phases of a transaction)
                    - Enhance PTP protocol response error cases (session already opened is
                      ok & wrong frame embedded size accepted when reception size is valid)
                    - Enhance PTP protocol to be able to process PTP events
                    - No more PTP close session when device binding already released
                    - Fixed bug: Crash at exit when device binding already released (ex:
                      device disconnected before exit)       

2006.01.16   V2.0   Public release.
                    - Canon Ixus 40 referenced and supported
                    - Canon A75, A85, A95, G5, G6, S50 and S60 referenced (untested)
                    - Kodak P850 referenced and supported
                    - Kodak CX6445, CX7220, CX7300, CX7310, CX7330, CX7525, CX7530,
                      DX7590, DX7630, LS663, LS753, Z730 and Z7590 referenced (untested)
                    - Nikon Coolpix 3200 and 3700 referenced and supported
                    - Most of Nikon camera devices referenced (untested)
                    - Default Nikon camera model to process unknown devices defined
                    - Tooltype and argument "PACKET_MAX_SIZE" as packet maximum size
                      during PTP data exchanges added (default 512 Ko)
                    - Tooltype and argument "RESP_ERR_RETRY_DELAY_MS", as waited delay
                      before to retry a failed response during PTP data reception
                      added (default 0 ms)
                    - Tooltype and argument "START_AUTO_SCAN" to control camera contents
                      automatic scan at starting (default TRUE)
                    - Automatic camera contents scan at program starting
                    - Add a list to display and select for action camera objects
                    - Use MUI requester for user notification/selection boxes
                    - Add PTP open session retry on error
                    - Priority of the PTP communication process is increased during a
                      PTP transaction
                    - Fixed bug: Use only one PTP session to avoid object id. changes
                    - Fixed bug: Compile with Gcc includes for -noixemul
                    - Fixed bug: Size in PTP send data frame corrected
                    - Fixed bug: Video number was updated insteed of sound number after
                      a sound delete completed action       

2004.09.26   V1.1   Public release.
                    - Kodak DX4530 supported
                    - Kodak CX7430 and LS743 referenced (untested)
                    - Canon EOS 300D referenced and supported
                    - Canon S1 IS, IXUS 500 referenced and supported
                    - Canon IXUS 400, IXUS 430 referenced (untested)
                    - Canon MV6i DV camera referenced (untested)
                    - Tooltype "SAVE_LOCATION" as default download path added
                    - User requester to save or skip, one or all existing file(s) added
                    - Write by part large files (more than 2 Mo)
                    - 10 Mo download limitation removed
                    - Fixed bug: File saving error is now correctly processed

2004.03.29   V1.0.1 Public release.
                    - Sony DSC-V1 supported
                    - Kodak CX6200 supported
                    - Kodak CX6230 referenced and supported
                    - Kodak CX4210, CX4230, CX4300, CX6330, DX4530 referenced (untested)
                    - Retry on error at data reception added
                    - Retry on error at response reception enhanced
                    - Fixed bug: File log version crash because of task concurrency
                    - Fixed bug: Directory selected with "/" gives wrong file name to save
                    - Fixed bug: AmigaOS crash at exit solved (-noixemul link option)

2004.02.10   V1.0   Public release.
                    - First AmigaOS/68k release
                    - Unknown camera models are now processed according to default
                      parameters defined for each vendor
                    - Kodak CX4200 and CX6200 referenced (untested)
                    - Fixed bug: User interface process message port was never released
                    - Fixed bug: Child process message port was not correctly released
                    - Fixed bug: Retry for PTP response reception was broken
                    - Internal changes for AmigaOS/68K release

2003.12.22   V0.9   Third public release.
                    - Camera serial number added
                    - Sounds management added (usefull for Canon camera)
                    - Canon A70 is supported
                    - Sony DSC-P52 is supported
                    - PTP protocol enhanced to take into account Sony and Canon
                      PTP limitations and specific capabilities
                    - Fixed bug: Status always display no video available
                    - Fixed bug: The 10 Mo input buffer was not released in
                                 previous release (oups!)

2003.11.10   V0.8   Second public release.
                    - Delete images and delete videos functions added
                    - Get and set camera current date added
                    - PTP Protocol completed with get thumbnail, delete object,
                      get object number, get property description, get property
                      value and set property value
                    - Source reworked to be shared with the future VHI driver

2003.10.11   V0.7   First public release.
                    - Kodak LS443 and DX3500 known as successfully supported
                    - Other Kodak digital camera known as untested

2003.10.05   V0.6   Beta-Test release.
                    - Progress bar enhanced with scale, info text and cancel
                      button
                    - Localization added, french catalog created
                    - Application menu added
                    - About program window added
                    - Application task priority changed to 5 in order to be
                      coherent with other USB driver priority level
                    - User interface moved into a specific task

2003.08.11   V0.5   Beta-Test release.
                    - Management of different PTP digital camera models
                      definition added (to request correct images or videos
                      format)
                    - Progress bar for download added
                    - PTP protocol error user notification added

2003.07.29   V0.4   Internal release.
                    - Video (QuickTime) download, currently limited to 10 Mo,
                      has been added
                    - Some user failure notification (requester) added

2003.07.26   V0.3   Internal release.
                    - A basic user interface is now available to select download
                      target drawer
                    - Few amoung of images in camera is now correctly supported

2003.07.20   V0.2a  Internal release compiled with MorphOS SDK V1.0p1.

2003.07.13   V0.2   Internal release allowing to download all the digital camera
                    images (No GUI yet).
                    - Image transfer packets maximum size limited at 512 Ko in
                      order to avoid crash

2003.06.18   V0.1   Initial internal release allowing to download the digital
                    camera first image (No GUI yet).

@endnode

@node "Bugs"

PtpDigCam software has the followings known problems:

--- General problems -----------------------------------------------------------

G001 - After a protocol error, PtpDigCam doesn't know very well how to drive
       the device to return a normal situation. Usually you must exit the
       program and restart it. It may be required to manually release the
       camera binding from the USB configuration panel and sometimes only
       a reboot will correctly release the binding to use the device again.
       Peharps it is a Poseidon issue too.

G002 - Camera disconnection event is not processed yet. Software may crach,
       please always exit the program before to disconnect the device.
       [SOLVE FROM RELEASE 2.0a]

--- MorphOS problems -----------------------------------------------------------

M001 - Some basic OS services like message port creation or process creation may
       fail. In this case, PtpDigCam is unable to run correctly and may crash.
       [WON'T BE SOLVED]

M002 - Sometimes, the user interface freezes with an "Application is mediating"
       window title.
       [SOLVED FROM RELEASE 2.0]

M003 - When Miami is running, the program is sometimes unable to create the
       progress bar process which is required for downloading or deleting.
       In this case, PtpDigCam is unable to run correctly and may crash.
       [SOLVED FROM RELEASE 2.0]

M004 - When Voyager is running, the program is unable to assume the required
       real time level to process PTP protocol exchange and may crash.
       [SOLVED FROM RELEASE 2.0]

--- AmigaOS problems -----------------------------------------------------------

A001 - When program started from Workbench, a Guru 0x80000008 may occur at exit.
       [SOLVED FROM RELEASE 1.0.1]

A002 - Unable to save images to a selected location other than default "RAM:".
       [SOLVE FROM RELEASE 1.0.1]

--- Devices problems -----------------------------------------------------------

D001 - Canon devices sometimes stops to answer a PTP delete command after the
       second image was deleted.
       [SOLVE FROM RELEASE 2.0a]

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@endnode

